What memory sticks out the most in your mind from filming in Grenada? The people I met were really nice. I will always have the memory of those in my mind when I think about Grenada.

How do you feel this film and the workshop will impact the lives of the Grenadian people today and in the future? I would like to think that this film will inspire someone to leave the safety zone of the film and try a different direction. When the workshops were taking place in our community – almost everyone in the community took a break from their daily routine to see what was going on – I guess that is one area that they can get out and learn something new.

Team Sitting Bull cast (Salim, Nancy & Mary) played in the award ceremony playing games bossing participants around and winning prizes but in the end everyone won. The camera department had the best prize as they were asked to play hockey in a full team sport.

This is the award the team presenting as Team Sitting Bull won – a one hour calvin Klein spray can by the pool. The Thinking Tank by the most liberal award team name.

The Public service award (for delivering a great presentation). The Hockey Lookout by Team Best Picture.
